git Manual

Description:
git allow us to recover deleted files.
git allows us to go back to specific version of file.
git allows teams to collectively create, modify and merge files.

Commands:
clone      Clone a git repository into a new directory
init       Create an empty git repository or reinitialize an existing one

add        Tell git to track content and stage for next commit
mv         Move or rename a file, a directory, or a symlink
reset      Reset current HEAD to the specified state
rm         Remove files from the working tree and from the index

commit     Save all the added changes to the git repository
diff       Show changes between commits, commit and working tree, etc

log        Show commit logs
status     Show the git working tree status

pull       Fetch changes from server and integrate with local code
push       Update remote git server with local changes
fetch      Fetch changes from server without integrating with local code.
